   "source": [
    "# RFM Customer Segmentation — Ditch\n",
    "**Brand:** Ditch | **Data:** Shopify Orders Export | **Period:** Apr 2025 – Apr 2026\n",
    "\n",
    "RFM scores every customer on three axes:\n",
    "- **Recency** — how recently they purchased\n",
    "- **Frequency** — how many orders they've placed\n",
    "- **Monetary** — how much they've spent total"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "165feb0b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup & Data Loading"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 51,
   "id": "5d7fbc57",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Loaded 95,282 rows across 54,830 order numbers\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.ticker as mticker\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from datetime import timedelta\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', palette='muted')\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 120\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('orders_cleaned.csv', low_memory=False)\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(df):,} rows across {df['Name'].nunique():,} order numbers\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9d4e9b0c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Cleaning\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Multi-line orders** — Shopify writes one row per line item, we deduplicate on order number\n",
    "- **Non-paid statuses** — keep `paid` only\n",
    "- **Cancelled orders** — dropped via `Cancelled at`\n",
    "- **Missing emails** — can't attribute to a customer, dropped\n",
    "- **Net revenue** — subtract refunded amount from order total"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 52,
   "id": "ea10b4c7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "After paid filter:       52,193 rows\n",
      "After cancel drop:       52,177 rows\n",
      "After email drop:        49,862 rows\n",
      "After dedup (orders):    49,862 unique orders\n",
      "After net revenue > 0:   49,411 orders\n",
      "\n",
      "Date range:  2025-04-01 → 2026-04-01\n",
      "Unique customers: 36,062\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "clean = df[df['Financial Status'] == 'paid'].copy()\n",
    "print(f\"After paid filter:       {len(clean):,} rows\")\n",
    "\n",
    "clean = clean[clean['Cancelled at'].isna()]\n",
    "print(f\"After cancel drop:       {len(clean):,} rows\")\n",
    "\n",
    "clean = clean[clean['Email'].notna()]\n",
    "print(f\"After email drop:        {len(clean):,} rows\")\n",
    "\n",
    "orders = clean.drop_duplicates(subset='Name')[['Name', 'Email', 'Created at', 'Total', 'Refunded Amount']].copy()\n",
    "print(f\"After dedup (orders):    {len(orders):,} unique orders\")\n",
    "\n",
    "orders['Refunded Amount'] = orders['Refunded Amount'].fillna(0)\n",
    "orders['net_total'] = orders['Total'] - orders['Refunded Amount']\n",
    "orders = orders[orders['net_total'] > 0]\n",
    "print(f\"After net revenue > 0:   {len(orders):,} orders\")\n",
    "\n",
    "orders['Created at'] = pd.to_datetime(orders['Created at'], utc=True)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nDate range:  {orders['Created at'].min().date()} → {orders['Created at'].max().date()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Unique customers: {orders['Email'].nunique():,}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6cd57a62",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. RFM Metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "Snapshot date = one day after the most recent order. Standard convention \n",
    "so the most recent buyer doesn't get a recency of 0, which would break \n",
    "the quintile scoring."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 53,
   "id": "8a9c8966",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
