     "execution_count": 53,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "snapshot = orders['Created at'].max() + timedelta(days=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "rfm = orders.groupby('Email').agg(\n",
    "    recency   = ('Created at', lambda x: (snapshot - x.max()).days),\n",
    "    frequency = ('Name',       'nunique'),\n",
    "    monetary  = ('net_total',  'sum')\n",
    ").reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Snapshot date: {snapshot.date()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"RFM table: {rfm.shape[0]:,} customers\")\n",
    "rfm[['recency', 'frequency', 'monetary']].describe().round(2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "88faaca1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Scoring (Quintiles 1–5)\n",
    "\n",
    "Each metric split into 5 equal buckets. Recency is **inverted** — \n",
    "bought yesterday = score 5, bought a year ago = score 1. `rank(method='first')` \n",
    "on Frequency handles the many ties at F=1 (most customers only ordered once)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 54,
   "id": "f88a24b0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Score distribution:\n",
      "rfm_score\n",
      "3      453\n",
      "4     1343\n",
      "5     2496\n",
      "6     3720\n",
      "7     4385\n",
      "8     4390\n",
      "9     4332\n",
      "10    3748\n",
      "11    3221\n",
      "12    2551\n",
      "13    1840\n",
      "14    1628\n",
      "15    1955\n",
      "Name: count, dtype: int64\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "rfm['R'] = pd.qcut(rfm['recency'],                        q=5, labels=[5,4,3,2,1], duplicates='drop')\n",
    "rfm['F'] = pd.qcut(rfm['frequency'].rank(method='first'), q=5, labels=[1,2,3,4,5])\n",
    "rfm['M'] = pd.qcut(rfm['monetary'],                       q=5, labels=[1,2,3,4,5], duplicates='drop')\n",
    "\n",
    "rfm['rfm_score'] = rfm[['R', 'F', 'M']].astype(int).sum(axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Score distribution:\")\n",
    "print(rfm['rfm_score'].value_counts().sort_index())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1fc0d674",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Segmentation\n",
    "\n",
    "| Segment | Logic | Action |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Champion | R≥4 & F≥4 | Reward, ask for reviews |\n",
    "| Loyal Customer | R≥3 & F≥3 | Upsell, early access |\n",
    "| New Customer | R≥4 & F≤2 | Second purchase campaign |\n",
    "| At Risk | R≤2 & F≥3 | Re-engagement email |\n",
    "| Win Back | R=1 & F≥2 | Last-chance discount |\n",
    "| One-Time Buyer | Everything else | Nurture sequence |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 55,
   "id": "b506a3c9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "segment\n",
      "At Risk           7974\n",
      "One-Time Buyer    7596\n",
      "Loyal Customer    6949\n",
      "Champion          6714\n",
      "New Customer      5146\n",
      "Win Back          1683\n",
      "Name: count, dtype: int64\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def label_segment(row):\n",
    "    r, f = int(row.R), int(row.F)\n",
    "    if   r >= 4 and f >= 4: return 'Champion'\n",
    "    elif r >= 3 and f >= 3: return 'Loyal Customer'\n",
    "    elif r >= 4 and f <= 2: return 'New Customer'\n",
    "    elif r <= 2 and f >= 3: return 'At Risk'\n",
    "    elif r == 1 and f >= 2: return 'Win Back'\n",
    "    else:                   return 'One-Time Buyer'\n",
    "\n",
    "rfm['segment'] = rfm.apply(label_segment, axis=1)\n",
    "print(rfm['segment'].value_counts())"
   ]
  },
